  "response": "To get an internship at IITs in December, follow these steps:\n\n1. Eligibility Criteria:\n- Be a current undergraduate or postgraduate student\n- Have a strong academic record\n- Meet specific department requirements\n\n2. Application Process:\n- Check IIT websites for internship opportunities\n- Look for specific internship programs\n- Apply through institute portals or online platforms\n\n3. Preparation:\n- Maintain good CGPA\n- Develop relevant technical skills\n- Learn programming languages\n- Create a strong resume\n- Prepare for potential interviews\n\n4. Networking:\n- Attend campus placement events\n- Connect with professors\n- Reach out to alumni\n- Use professional networking sites like LinkedIn\n\n5. Specific Channels:\n- IIT Internship Portals\n- NEAT (National Employability Enhancement Mission)\n- IIPC (Institute Industry Placement Cell)\n- Research internship programs\n- Summer internship programs\n\n6. Recommended Websites:\n- Internshala\n- LinkedIn\n- IIT official websites\n- NPTEL\n- Academic department portals\n\n7. Timing:\n- Start preparing early\n- Apply between September-November\n- Be proactive and persistent\n\nTailor your approach to specific IIT requirements and showcase your skills effectively.",
